Fire gutted part of Local Government House along Selous Avenue in Harare Friday afternoon destroying property worth thousands of dollars.The fire is believed to have been caused by an electric fault involving some cables connected to a transformerHarare Fire Brigade battle to extinguish the fire engulfing Local Government House, it is believed that the fire was caused by an electrician trying to fix cables to a transformer.-(Picture by Tawanda Mudimu)Property worth thousands were destroyed after Local Government House caught fire in Harare , it is believed that the fire was caused by an electrician trying to fix cables to a transformer.-(Picture by Tawanda Mudimu)Harare Fire Brigade battle to extinguish the fire engulfing Local Government House, it is believed that the fire was caused by an electrician trying to fix cables to a transformer.-(Picture by Tawanda Mudimu)&nbsp; 